# Code ownership for review routing.
#
# Slate is a single monorepo: one Rust core + one FFI surface, consumed by
# per-platform native frontends under apps/. See docs/plans/13_repo_structure.md.
# Per-area ownership is expressed here (not via separate repositories); as
# platform maintainers join, add them to the matching app line — no restructuring.
#
# Syntax: <path glob>  <owner...>   (last matching pattern wins)

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
*                               @coryj627

# --- Shared Rust core (the only code shared across all platforms) ---
/crates/slate-core/             @coryj627
/crates/slate-uniffi/           @coryj627

# --- Per-platform frontends (add platform maintainers here as they join) ---
/apps/slate-mac/                @coryj627
/apps/slate-windows/            @coryj627
/apps/slate-ios/                @coryj627
/apps/slate-android/            @coryj627

# --- Cross-cutting: build, CI, licensing, architecture ---
/scripts/                       @coryj627
/.github/                       @coryj627
/docs/plans/                    @coryj627
/Cargo.toml                     @coryj627
/LICENSE                        @coryj627
